A/B Testing Analysis - Data Cleaning & Statistical Testing

performs data cleaning, feature engineering, and statistical testing
for A/B testing analysis (Control vs Test campaign).

import pandas as pd

1. Load Data

control = pd.read_csv('data/control_group.csv')
test = pd.read_csv('data/test_group.csv')

 2. Initial Cleaning
=Fix column name issue if exists
control.columns = control.columns.str.replace(']', '', regex=False)

= Add group labels
control['group'] = 'control'
test['group'] = 'test'

= Combine datasets
df = pd.concat([control, test], ignore_index=True)

= Standardize column names
df.columns = [
    'campaign_name',
    'date',
    'spend_usd',
    'impressions',
    'reach',
    'website_clicks',
    'searches',
    'view_content',
    'add_to_cart',
    'purchases',
    'group'
]


3. Data Cleaning

= Convert date column
df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date'], errors='coerce')

= Handle missing values
df = df.dropna(subset=['website_clicks', 'purchases'])

= Remove invalid rows (avoid division errors)
df = df[(df['website_clicks'] > 0) & (df['purchases'] >= 0)]

= 4. Feature Engineering

df['ctr'] = df['website_clicks'] / df['impressions']
df['conversion_rate'] = df['purchases'] / df['website_clicks']
df['cpa'] = df['spend_usd'] / df['purchases']

= Replace infinite values
df.replace([float('inf'), -float('inf')], pd.NA, inplace=True)

= 5. Aggregated Metrics

summary = df.groupby('group').agg({
    'spend_usd': 'sum',
    'website_clicks': 'sum',
    'purchases': 'sum'
})

summary['conversion_rate'] = summary['purchases'] / summary['website_clicks']
summary['cpa'] = summary['spend_usd'] / summary['purchases']

print("\n=== Summary Metrics ===")
print(summary)


 6. Statistical Test (Z-test)

control_clicks = summary.loc['control', 'website_clicks']
control_purchases = summary.loc['control', 'purchases']

test_clicks = summary.loc['test', 'website_clicks']
test_purchases = summary.loc['test', 'purchases']

